This paper is about evaluating machine reading comprehension models on multiple datasets, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses various training paradigms and representation learning, which are common topics in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions using synthetic augmentations for the datasets, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
